what's the best rodent for a pet something small and cuddly but easy to take care of gerbils i own two gerbils are great they are dinural so are awake night and day they get very excited about any new thing you put into the tank for them and will immediately explore it you can make cardboard buildings tunnels for them and they will love crawling into through over and on them then they will gnaw it all up you can house two for a gallon set up they are by far the cleanest of all the small pets so bedding is not a big expense they live in clans and groom nest play together you can house up to seven boys in one tank five gallons of space per gerbil they are easy to breed and both mother and father are great parents gerbils come in about colors and varieties they are not a big commitment as the life span is about years good luck on choosing the perfect pet i hope you get to experience the joy of owning pet gerbils p s gerbils are better than hamsters Gerbil Meriones unguiculatus Fancy rat Ferret Pet Guinea pig Goldfish Domestic rabbit Rodent Cat The Adventures of Pete & Pete Animal communication The Pet Sounds Sessions About a Boy Narbonic Muroidea Pet Sounds Pet skunk Rat One Tree Hill (TV series) Neopets Dog Sin City Lemmiwinks Ren and Stimpy Pet Shop Boys Chinchilla Recurring South Park characters Tarantula Discus (fish) Calvin and Hobbes Blankets (graphic novel) Brown Rat Bird AFI 100 Years series Little Britain Shaggy dog story The Fairly OddParents W.I.T.C.H. Wolfenstein: Enemy Territory Quicksort The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Betta (Siamese Fighting Fish) Autonomous building Grief Dog training The Jazz Singer Book of Isaiah Marriage The Dukes of Hazzard Chihuahua (dog) Care Bears Good Vibrations Ra (board game) The Young Ones (TV series) Platypus Sex and the City Pet store Social rule Stalag Luft III Eric Cartman Brewery Gaia Online Sid Vicious The Lovely Bones Butters Stotch Mountaineering Super Metroid Marine aquarium Dog agility Jon Secada Golden Hamster Hy